[The 1 new confirmed case in the past 24 hours was imported, and it is now 10 days that no new cases have been reported from Beijing.

There were 2 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals (1 imported) and no new conversions from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. Since 18 May 2020, China has reported 37 cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic infection.

Hong Kong reported 19 new cases. The newly reported cases involve 8 males and 11 females aged between 17 and 75 years. Among them, 5 had travel history during the incubation period (https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202007/15/P2020071500824.htm). Hong Kong has implemented new restrictions: 1) masks mandatory on public transport; 2) dine-in services banned 6 pm to 5 am, maximum 4/table; 3) bars, gyms, karaoke lounges, and amusement parks closed; public gatherings back from 50 to 4 people maximum; 4) passengers from high-risk countries must produce proof of negative PCR before boarding flight to Hong Kong (https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/health-environment/article/3092920/coronavirus-hong-kong-toughen-social-distancing).

Takeaway message: China continues to have importations of infected individuals with SARS-CoV-2. Hong Kong is dealing with increased local transmission associated with the lifting of restrictions; new severe restrictions have been announced.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7580042,155. - Mod.UBA]

