[In the past 24 hours, according to the report at the source URL, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 61 cases with 2 new deaths, compared with 39 cases and 0 new deaths in the previous day (14 Jul 2020). The daily newly confirmed case count has been at or below 100 for 93 consecutive days. There were 14 locally transmitted cases: Seoul (6), Gyeonggi (3), Incheon (2), Gwangju (1), Daejeon (1), Gangwon (1); and 47 imported cases: airport quarantine (20), Gyeonggi (18), Deagu (2), Gangwon (2), Seoul (1), Ulsan (1), Incheon (1), Chungbuk (1), and Gyeongnam (1). Seven provinces reported no newly confirmed cases (compared with 12 provinces yesterday, 14 Jul 2020).

The overall impression hasn't changed: Lifting of measures has been accompanied by increases in locally acquired infections through increasing clusters related to gatherings of people at employment (bringing it outside employment to contacts) and in houses of worship, and bars and clubs. However, that being said, importations are also playing a major role in the country as well.

